Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) and @carrot{1}(peeled and chopped), chop the @celery stick{1}(chopped) and @garlic clove{2}(chopped). Peel and slice the @potato{1}(peeled and sliced into discs) into discs less than ½cm thick (basically as thin as you can cut them).

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on a mediumlow heat. Cook the onion, carrot, celery and garlic. Add the @bay leaf{1} and the @thyme{1%sprig}. After around ~{5%minutes} the ingredients will have softened up.

> Tip: Pinch the thyme stalk between your fingers and run your fingers along it to strip off the leaves.

Add in the @baby spinach{3%leaves} and cook it for ~{1-2%minutes} or until it has wilted.

Drain and rinse the @organic lentils{1%can} and stir them into the onion mixture along with the @chopped tomatoes{1%can} and the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Let the mixture bubble away until you have a nice thick sauce.

Once the water from the sauce has disappeared, remove the bay leaves. Stir through all of the @ricotta cheese{250%g} quickly until you have a smooth sauce. Then immediately take the pan off the heat.

Pop half the lentil mixture in an #ovenproof dish{} and cover this with a layer of potatoes. Spoon over the other half of the lentil mixture and add another layer of potatoes. Bake with a lid on for ~{30%minutes}.

Give your kitchen a quick tidy and put your feet up until dinner is ready.

After 30 mins, if you can slide a #knife{} easily into the potatoes then they are cooked. If not, give them another ~{5%minutes}. Once they are cooked, turn off your oven and pre-heat your #grill{} to high. Sprinkle the @hard Italian style cheese{3%dispensed}(grated) on top of the moussaka. Put it under your grill until it browns.

Serve the moussaka and enjoy!